The course provides an overview of the most common psychiatric disorders in the adult population, discusses possible problems and peculiarities in the physiotherapeutic treatment of patients with mental disorders, and learns to apply various therapeutic techniques in the treatment of patients with mental disorders.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide students with knowledge and practical skills for working in physiotherapy with psychiatrically ill patients.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student: - is able to recognize and communicate with a patient with psychiatric disorders; - knows possible obstacles occurring during therapy process with psychiatric patients and is able to find solutions; - knows the most common psychiatric disorders among adults and their main symptoms; - implements a variety of therapies to treat patients with psychiatric disorders.
